# Git workflow

Solo-dev project — default to committing directly on `main`.

## Default

- Commit and push to `main` unless the user explicitly asks otherwise.
- Do **not** create a feature branch or open a PR on your own initiative.

## Use a branch or PR only when

- The user creates a separate branch themselves, or
- The user asks you to create a separate branch, or
- The user asks you to create a PR.

## Commits

- Still follow Conventional Commits for messages.
- Split into logical commits when the change set warrants it.
- Only create commits when the user asks (see user commit rule).
